:"<img src=\"https://pixel.nymag.com/imgs/daily/intelligencer/2016/12/02/02-moving-sidewalk-toronto.w700.h467.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fpixel.nymag.com%2Fimgs%2Fdaily%2Fintelligencer%2F2016%2F12%2F02%2F02-moving-sidewalk-toronto.w700.h467.jpg&h=f9d83a08&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\nThe high-speed ThyssenKrupp &ldquo;Express Walkway&rdquo; at the Toronto airport is considered the fastest-moving sidewalk in the world, with an expanding pallet design that accelerates after picking up passengers. Photo: Frank Elschner/Courtesy of thyssenKrupp<br />\n<br />\nreference:<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moving_walkway#ThyssenKrupp_Express_Walkway\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FMoving_walkway%23ThyssenKrupp_Express_Walkway&d=tFviIiuTv25K9aUiQ%2BXN3Dw60zqfRdeCYg0zJNkavsY%3D&h=d7fdaa8d\" target=\"_blank\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moving_walkway#ThyssenKrupp_Express_Walkway</a><br />\nIt moves at roughly 2 km/h (1.2 mph) when riders step onto it and speeds up to approximately 7 km/h (4.3 mph), which it remains at until near the end, where it slows back down.<br />\n最高速都7km/h  其實慢線 push到上10km/h 並唔係問題<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WRX_CJvfYyU\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DWRX_CJvfYyU&d=tFviIiuTv25K9aUiQ%2BXN3Dw60zqfRdeCYg0zJNkavsY%3D&h=2efc458e\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WRX_CJvfYyU</a><br />\n7km/h 感覺其實都仲係慢"},{"pid":"f925db9b263c801af8a4112d105ad0926d0cf8d4","tid":1071166,"uid":90183,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"95bc3140ca237e2cd3e05c1a64b4f43b4f68944f","tid":1071166,"uid":64994,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"1b3ad090f475470f6a811c60e0a522880a074aaa","tid":1071166,"uid":90183,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"79d46db52d19eb7e09cfb3b4156934a234679e73","tid":1071166,"uid":78755,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"